<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018291>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Cymbasoma norvegicum sp. n. from off Norway, adult female holotype; ventral view of whole specimen. Image from confocal laser scanning microscopy (CLSM). (a) habitus, semi-ventral view. Abbreviations: 1–3, furcal setae on left ramus; A1, antennule; as, anal somite; bs, basipodal seta; nlp, nipple-like process; oc, oral cone; osp, ovigerous spines; P1–P4, legs 1–4; S1–S4, purported position of antennule segments 1–4. White dots indicate position of intercoxal sclerite of leg1. Scale bar: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018291/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10018295>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Cymbasoma norvegicum sp. n. from off Norway, adult female holotype. (a) forehead corrugation, ventral view; (b) antennule showing setal armature following Grygier and Ohtsuka′s (1995) nomenclature, ventral view; (c) fifth legs showing inner and outer lobes, semi-lateral view; (d) fifth pedigerous and genital somites with fifth legs and proximal part of ovigerous spines, ventral view; (e) P1 third exopodal segment showing armature and ornamentation of outermost apical spiniform seta; (f) furca showing armature on left and right rami, ventral view. Abbreviations: S1–S4, purported antennule segments 1–4. Scale bars: 50 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10018295/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

